Attribute.value: Buffer Overflow in Local Command-Line Utilities
This attack targets command-line utilities available in a number of shells. An attacker can leverage a vulnerability found in a command-line utility to escalate privilege to root.
The target hosst exposes a command-line utility to the user. The command-line utility exposed by the target host has a buffer overflow vulnerability that can be exploited.
Carefully review the service's implementation before making it available to users.
